race.comment: MISS TOP GUN (4) is a locally trained mare who looks very well placed here. Raced on speed and placed fresh then placed again last time. Aided by the claim and on her home track will sit handy and should go close. SUNBURNT (6) looks the main danger. Was runner-up fresh then finished 11th here last time but was beaten less than three lengths in a very bunched finish. Is a third-up winner and this is easier. Gets chance to score. GRASSMERE JEWEL (1) is a lightly raced mare with a huge weight. Best form is at this trip and has placed 3/5 course and distance. They didn't claim and stuck with a senior but despite the hefty impost is among the main hopes on best form. MISS REMSKI (7) is overdue for a win and will be on speed. Best form is on firmer footing but has the ability.
